# Authoring Morphic Cards & Editors

## Every card MUST
- Extend the shared **`MorphicCard`** base (`src/shared/base-card.ts`) — do not subclass
  `LitElement` directly. The base provides the accent engine, gradient + icon-morph tokens,
  and the responsive/sections plumbing.
- Implement **`getGridOptions()`** returning a sensible default plus `min_columns` /
  `min_rows`. Lay out with **container queries** against the card root
  (`container-type: inline-size`) — never fixed `px` widths.
- Provide `static getConfigElement()`, `static getStubConfig()`, and register itself in
  `window.customCards` (handled via the `registerMorphicCard()` helper).
- Style **only** from tokens (`--morphic-*`, `--md-sys-color-*`) with native HA-var
  fallbacks. Never hardcode hex colors.

## Use the inherited features
- **Accent**: call `this.accent` / set `this.colorKey`; default `color_key` is the card
  title/name. Honor precedence: `color:` > `color_key:` > title > `entity_id`.
- **Gradient**: apply `var(--morphic-accent-fill)` for the subtle accent → primary fill;
  keep text on `--md-sys-color-on-surface` legible.
- **Icon-morph**: use the base `iconShape` state (`circle` for OFF/inactive, `squircle`
  for ON/active) — this is the signature interaction; animate the morph.

## Every editor MUST
- Extend the shared **editor base** (`src/editors/base-editor.ts`) and render with
  **`ha-form`** + selectors (`ha-entity-picker`, `ha-selector`, ...). **No raw YAML blob.**
- Be mobile-first, M3-token styled, with grouped/collapsible sections, clear labels,
  helper text, sane defaults, and a working live preview.
- Fire `config-changed` via the base `dispatchConfig()` helper; never mutate config in place.

## Example: grid options
```typescript
getGridOptions(): MorphicGridOptions {
  return { columns: 6, rows: 3, min_columns: 4, min_rows: 2 };
}
```

## Don'ts
- No fixed pixel layout, no theme/`--md-sys-color-*` overrides, no targeting another
  card's shadow DOM, no reimplementing Bubble Card / navbar-card.
